<h1>Who was Gregor Mendel</h1>
<p>Gregor Mendel was born on July 22, 1822 in Czechoslovakia. 
Mendel was sent to the school Lipnik in 1831 and to the grammar school in Opava at the age of 12.
In 1843, Mendel was admitted to the Augustinian order in Brno. Mendel took courses in agriculture, pomiculture and vine growing while at Brno.
Mendel became a teacher of mathematics and Greek in 1849. However he failed his university exam. 
Mendel started to perform heredity experiments after performing the same experiments his professor performed.
For many years, he was focused on heredity. Gregor Mendel died on January 6, 1884.</p>
